NAME
       printf, fprintf, snprintf, vsnprintf - formatted output

SYNOPSIS
       #include <stdio.h>

       int  printf(const char *fmt, ...);
       int  fprintf(FILE *stream, const char *fmt, ...);
       int  snprintf(char *buf, size_t n, const char *fmt, ...);
       int  vsnprintf(char *buf, size_t n, const char *fmt, va_list ap);

DESCRIPTION
       libcervus implements a printf family for freestanding user code.
       Userspace programs are built with SSE enabled, so floating point
       conversions (%f / %e / %g) and variadic doubles work normally.

SUPPORTED CONVERSIONS
       %d %i %u %o %x %X     signed/unsigned integers
       %ld %lu %lx %lld %llu %llx
                             long and long long variants
       %s %c %p              string, char, pointer
       %f %e %g %F %E %G     floating point
       %%                    literal percent

FLAGS
       -  +  ' '  0  #         standard left-align, sign, space, zero pad
       *                        width or precision from the argument list

RETURN VALUE
       Number of bytes written (snprintf: that would have been written
       had n been large enough). Negative on error.

SEE ALSO
       fputs(3), write(2)
